parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected braking of the vehicle at highway speeds can lead to accidents, rear-end collisions, and road rage incidents, putting the driver and other road users at risk.
symptoms: The vehicle brakes abruptly without warning
often when there are no other cars or obstacles in sight
causing the driver and passengers to experience whiplash and displacement of items in the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the autopilot system can cause the vehicle to deviate from its lane, slow down or speed up unexpectedly, and fail to detect pedestrians or other obstacles, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to stay in its lane
drives slowly into the next lane
or fails to detect pedestrians or other obstacles
causing accidents and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cruise Control and Lane Guidance Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control and lane guidance systems can cause the vehicle to slow down or speed up unexpectedly, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle changes speed unexpectedly
signals and changes lanes without warning
or fails to maintain its lane
causing the driver to lose control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the FSD system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's FSD system fails to function properly
causing the vehicle to slow down or speed up unexpectedly
deviate from its lane
or fail to detect pedestrians or other obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected braking of the vehicle can cause accidents, especially on highways, and lead to rear-end collisions, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly brakes or decelerates without warning
often on highways
even when there are no obstacles or vehicles in front of it. This can cause items in the vehicle to shift
and passengers to be thrown forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
often when the driver is attempting to slow down or stop. This can cause the vehicle to crash into objects or other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of cruise control and autopilot systems can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if the driver is not paying attention to the road.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to function properly
causing the vehicle to suddenly brake or accelerate without warning. The autopilot system may also malfunction
causing the vehicle to brake or accelerate unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected braking or acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, including rear-end collisions, and pose a significant risk to the safety of the driver, passengers, and other road users.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly brakes or accelerates without warning
often when there are no obstacles or vehicles in front of it
and may occur when using cruise control
autopilot
or adaptive cruise control features. The braking can be sudden and severe
causing the vehicle to decelerate rapidly
and may be accompanied by a sudden jolt or jerk.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Advanced Driver-Assistance Systems (ADAS) can cause the vehicle to behave erratically, leading to accidents and posing a risk to the safety of the driver, passengers, and other road users.
symptoms: The ADAS system may detect non-existent objects
issue false collision alerts
and trigger phantom braking or unintended acceleration. The system may also malfunction when making lane changes
causing the vehicle to shake violently or fishtail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lag or stuttering of the rear view camera can reduce the driver's visibility, making it difficult to detect obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The rear view camera displays a delayed or stuttering image
making it difficult for the driver to see what is behind the vehicle.
